 variant of   Wong  .","Cambodian: written វ៉ុន, unexplained."],"variants":[{"name":"Vaughan","meanings":["Welsh: from <i>fychan</i>, a lenited form of <i>bychan</i>, a diminutive of <i>bach</i> ‘little’. This was often used to distinguish the younger of two bearers of the same personal name, typically the son of a father with the same name."]}]},{"name":"Mathilde","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’."],"variants":[{"name":"Mechtild","meanings":["from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’."]},{"name":"Matilda","meanings":["Latinized form of a Germanic personal name derived from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."]},{"name":"Mechtilde","meanings":["Latinized form of a Germanic personal name derived from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1353272,"age":3,"year":"1060","julianDay":2108217,"description":"Svend II forms Danish church.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Mathilde von Odenkirchen was born about 1057. She married Adalbert von Saffenberg about 1090. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. She died in 1115, in Denmark, at the age of 59, and was buried in Wetter (Ruhr), Ennepe-Ruhr-Kreis, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany."},"et":{"about 1057–1115":"umbes 1057–1115","1053–1109":"1053–1109","1087–1152":"1087–1152","1091–1147":"1091–1147","1097–1177":"1097–1177","1057–1115":"1057–1115","1091":"1091","about 1091":"umbes 1091","1087":"1087","1097":"1097","1152":"1152","1053":"1053","UM 1090":"umbes 1090","1060":"1060","UM 1073":"umbes 1073","1115":"1115","1147":"1147","1057":"1057","1177":"1177","about 1057":"umbes 1057","16 DEC 1109":"16. detsember 1109","1109":"1109","Wetter, North Rhine-Westphalia Germany":"Wetter (Ruhr), Ennepe-Ruhr-Kreis, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Saksamaa","Heimbach, Jülich":"Heimbach, Jülich","Saffenberg, Germany":"Saksamaa","Denemarken":"Taani","Nörvenich, Kreis Düren, Rhineland, Prussia":"Nörvenich, Kreis Düren, Rheinprovinz, Preußen"},"fi":{"about 1057–1115":"noin 1057–1115","1053–1109":"1053–1109","1087–1152":"1087–1152","1091–1147":"1091–1147","1097–1177":"1097–1177","1057–1115":"1057–1115","1091":"1091","about 1091":"noin 1091","1087":"1087","1097":"1097","1152":"1152","1053":"1053","UM 1090":"noin 1090","1060":"1060","UM 1073":"noin 1073","1115":"1115","1147":"1147","1057":"1057","1177":"1177","about 1057":"noin 1057","16 DEC 1109":"16. joulukuuta 1109","1109":"1109","Wetter, North Rhine-Westphalia Germany":"Wetter (Ruhr), Ennepe-Ruhr-Kreis, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Saksa","Heimbach, Jülich":"Heimbach, Jülich","Saffenberg, Germany":"Saksa","Denemarken":"Tanska","Nörvenich, Kreis Düren, Rhineland, Prussia":"Nörvenich, Kreis Düren, Rheinprovinz, Preußen"},"fr":{"about 1057–1115":"environ 1057–1115","1053–1109":"1053–1109","1